Hand over the traitors!

816
01:13:39,840 --> 01:13:41,398
Return Tsingtao!

817
01:13:41,600 --> 01:13:44,637
Hand over the traitors!

818
01:13:45,240 --> 01:13:47,117
Charge!

819
01:13:47,320 --> 01:13:50,153
Charge!

820
01:13:56,600 --> 01:13:59,319
Go inside and grab the traitors!

821
01:13:59,520 --> 01:14:02,034
Open up...

822
01:14:02,200 --> 01:14:04,430
Open the door!

823
01:14:29,040 --> 01:14:30,712
We were under siege in Japan,

824
01:14:31,160 --> 01:14:33,355
it's happening here as well!

825
01:14:35,320 --> 01:14:37,959
Don't cry!

826
01:14:38,360 --> 01:14:40,874
Look, Ping-hsiang!

827
01:14:41,560 --> 01:14:43,869
Don't worry, I'm here.

828
01:14:46,440 --> 01:14:47,350
3 Bamboos!

829
01:15:00,920 --> 01:15:02,512
K'uang Hu-sheng, bravo!

830
01:15:03,120 --> 01:15:09,719
Jump!

831
01:15:09,880 --> 01:15:10,869
Jump inside!

832
01:15:19,360 --> 01:15:20,395
Soldiers!

833
01:15:22,320 --> 01:15:23,639
Teng Chung-hsia, Fang Ho!

834
01:15:25,240 --> 01:15:26,719
Go, Fang Ho!

835
01:15:27,760 --> 01:15:29,432
1...2...3...

836
01:15:30,680 --> 01:15:34,150
1...2...3...

837
01:15:36,080 --> 01:15:39,755
Quiet...

838
01:15:39,920 --> 01:15:42,559
You should be fighting Japanese in Shantung

839
01:15:42,720 --> 01:15:45,951
instead of guarding a traitor's house.

840
01:15:47,600 --> 01:15:49,989
Comrades! Brothers...

841
01:15:50,440 --> 01:15:51,509
We're one family!

842
01:15:52,280 --> 01:15:54,271
I believe we're one family,

843
01:15:55,040 --> 01:15:58,271
Those you're holding off

844
01:15:58,640 --> 01:16:01,313
are your brothers and sisters.

845
01:16:01,640 --> 01:16:04,632
Each and every one a patriotic student.

846
01:16:04,800 --> 01:16:07,837
Move aside, let us through!

847
01:16:08,000 --> 01:16:11,675
Protect our territory!

848
01:16:11,840 --> 01:16:14,434
Protect our sovereignty!

849
01:16:15,680 --> 01:16:16,556
Brothers!

850
01:16:16,720 --> 01:16:19,757
Everyone of you is patriotic

851
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:20,671
Am I right?

852
01:16:20,840 --> 01:16:21,670
Yes!

853
01:16:22,800 --> 01:16:24,552
Are you Chinese?

854
01:16:24,720 --> 01:16:25,516
Yes!

855
01:16:25,720 --> 01:16:27,517
Then let us through!

856
01:16:27,680 --> 01:16:30,319
Charge!

857
01:16:31,840 --> 01:16:32,670
Students!

858
01:16:32,840 --> 01:16:33,716
Tell me where he is!

859
01:16:33,880 --> 01:16:36,269
Hand over the traitor!

860
01:16:36,440 --> 01:16:38,510
Search the house! Step aside...

861
01:16:38,680 --> 01:16:41,399
Students...

862
01:16:41,960 --> 01:16:43,791
Listen, harbouring traitors

863
01:16:43,960 --> 01:16:45,837
makes you also a traitor of China.

864
01:16:46,840 --> 01:16:47,670
He's here!

865
01:16:50,160 --> 01:16:51,036
Students!

866
01:16:52,720 --> 01:16:53,948
I have nothing to do with it!

867
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:55,076
Where is Chang Tsung-hsiang?

868
01:16:55,240 --> 01:16:56,116
I don't know!

869
01:16:56,280 --> 01:16:57,110
Take him away!

870
01:17:00,840 --> 01:17:01,636
Listen...

871
01:17:01,800 --> 01:17:03,711
This is the desk on which the treaty was signed!

872
01:17:04,000 --> 01:17:12,510
Burn it...

873
01:17:12,680 --> 01:17:13,874
The police are here!

874
01:17:29,760 --> 01:17:31,273
Are you Ts'ao Ju-lin?

875
01:17:31,440 --> 01:17:32,759
No, I am not...

876
01:17:32,920 --> 01:17:34,353
- No? Then who are you? - I'm really nobody,

877
01:17:34,560 --> 01:17:36,790
just a visiting guest.

878
01:17:39,760 --> 01:17:41,318
Where did they go?

879
01:17:41,520 --> 01:17:42,157
They left.

880
01:17:42,320 --> 01:17:44,629
How could you! That's Chang Tsung-hsiang!

881
01:17:44,800 --> 01:17:45,596
After him...

882
01:18:19,560 --> 01:18:20,515
Let me go!

883
01:18:24,520 --> 01:18:26,795
Let me go!

884
01:18:27,520 --> 01:18:28,714
Let me go!

885
01:19:00,160 --> 01:19:02,355
Consider China's 2,000-year-old history,

886
01:19:02,800 --> 01:19:04,119
have you ever heard of

887
01:19:04,520 --> 01:19:06,875
students involved in arson and killing?

888
01:19:07,240 --> 01:19:09,435
They have no choice but to revolt.

889
01:19:10,400 --> 01:19:11,355
Today...

890
01:19:11,640 --> 01:19:15,349
President Hsu has arrested innocent students.

891
01:19:15,560 --> 01:19:18,916
He did it to please our enemies.

892
01:19:19,360 --> 01:19:21,271
As a staff member of the school,

893
01:19:21,280 --> 01:19:23,510
I declare the school will go on strike

894
01:19:23,520 --> 01:19:26,273
until the students are released.

895
01:19:26,440 --> 01:19:29,352
Long live students...

896
01:19:29,520 --> 01:19:32,796
Long live revolution...

897
01:19:54,720 --> 01:19:55,709
What is it?

898
01:19:57,760 --> 01:20:00,513
You wrote "The spirit of the Chinese People"

899
01:20:00,680 --> 01:20:02,352
and I admired you for it.

900
01:20:04,440 --> 01:20:05,509
Speaking of principles,

901
01:20:05,520 --> 01:20:08,398
you should know our differences with foreigners.

902
01:20:09,920 --> 01:20:10,989
But today,

903
01:20:11,400 --> 01:20:13,197
you wrote in a Japanese-owned newspaper

904
01:20:13,400 --> 01:20:16,551
denouncing the students as barbaric mobsters!

905
01:20:18,040 --> 01:20:20,076
What has happened to your principles?

906
01:20:22,600 --> 01:20:24,238
You're siding with the enemy.

907
01:20:44,440 --> 01:20:48,513
Students, workers and merchants are all on strike.

908
01:20:48,840 --> 01:20:52,833
Overnight, the whole country is in uproar.

909
01:20:54,440 --> 01:20:56,954
Even soldiers are siding with the students.

910
01:20:57,120 --> 01:21:00,396
This is a crucial moment, no compromise!

911
01:21:00,600 --> 01:21:03,956
We mustn't go against the tide.

912
01:22:02,960 --> 01:22:04,951
Tu-hsiu, what is it?

913
01:22:06,600 --> 01:22:07,953
Have we won already?

914
01:22:08,560 --> 01:22:10,232
Is this time for celebration?

915
01:22:11,080 --> 01:22:12,149
Ridiculous!

916
01:22:46,440 --> 01:22:47,509
Mr. Hu,

917
01:22:48,120 --> 01:22:52,079
are you denouncing Ch'en Tu-hsiu and Li Ta-chao?

918
01:22:57,360 --> 01:22:58,793
Why not?

919
01:22:59,640 --> 01:23:01,039
You must have a sound argument.

920
01:23:01,720 --> 01:23:05,793
Marx's doctrine is just a theory.

921
01:23:06,280 --> 01:23:07,554
But such a theory

922
01:23:07,640 --> 01:23:10,791
though proven successful in Russia

923
01:23:11,040 --> 01:23:14,237
does not mean it's applicable in China.

924
01:23:15,320 --> 01:23:18,073
We must not act like a parrot

925
01:23:18,240 --> 01:23:20,879
and lose ourselves by following others.

926
01:23:21,040 --> 01:23:22,632
To sit back and talk about theories

927
01:23:23,320 --> 01:23:25,515
without solving the actual problems

928
01:23:26,680 --> 01:23:28,352
is no different from Confucianism.

929
01:23:28,560 --> 01:23:31,438
If this is what New Culture is about,

930
01:23:31,840 --> 01:23:33,398
then it's meaningless.

931
01:23:34,080 --> 01:23:37,834
For Ch'en and Li to model on Russia,

932
01:23:38,520 --> 01:23:42,399
it's not going to solve our problems.

933
01:23:43,240 --> 01:23:44,275
You're wrong, sir.

934
01:23:44,640 --> 01:23:46,915
Confucianism is a feudal code,

935
01:23:47,200 --> 01:23:49,077
Whereas Marx's doctrine is scientific.

936
01:23:49,240 --> 01:23:50,958
You can't compare the two.

937
01:24:11,840 --> 01:24:13,193
Esteemed delegates,

938
01:24:14,440 --> 01:24:19,912
what right do you have to give Shantung to Japan?

939
01:24:20,520 --> 01:24:22,033
I am furious.

940
01:24:22,960 --> 01:24:30,833
Chinese people will never forget this painful day.

941
01:24:38,720 --> 01:24:40,233
You wouldn't dare to kill Ch'en Tu-hsiu!

942
01:24:40,840 --> 01:24:43,229
If he dies, there'll be hundreds more like him.

943
01:24:43,520 --> 01:24:46,318
Tell Hsu not to make himself a public enemy.

944
01:24:46,520 --> 01:24:48,590
If he still wants to continue as President,

945
01:24:48,760 --> 01:24:50,113
he must release Ch'en Tu-hsiu at once.

946
01:25:14,440 --> 01:25:17,238
You have suffered, Tu-hsiu.

947
01:25:24,440 --> 01:25:28,035
Ch'en Tu-hsiu takes on the burden alone,

948
01:25:28,800 --> 01:25:30,631
and sets an example for us all.

949
01:25:32,240 --> 01:25:36,028
Peking University is proud of him.

950
01:25:38,520 --> 01:25:40,590
Bravo, Mr. Ch'en!

951
01:26:03,120 --> 01:26:04,394
So sorry...

952
01:26:04,600 --> 01:26:06,431
- Over here! - What took you so long?

953
01:26:06,640 --> 01:26:07,959
We got lost!

954
01:26:09,760 --> 01:26:11,113
- Hello! - We'll do the introductions later,

955
01:26:11,280 --> 01:26:12,156
Iet's get on board.

956
01:26:12,320 --> 01:26:13,548
Come on...

957
01:26:14,000 --> 01:26:14,637
Let's go!

958
01:26:14,920 --> 01:26:15,909
Wait...

959
01:26:17,640 --> 01:26:18,516
I'm thinking...

960
01:26:18,920 --> 01:26:20,797
transplanting the experience of
a foreign revolution

961
01:26:21,400 --> 01:26:22,594
does it really work?

962
01:26:22,800 --> 01:26:23,710
Changed your mind again?

963
01:26:23,880 --> 01:26:26,075
China has much more complex issues,

964
01:26:26,800 --> 01:26:28,074
I'd better stay.

965
01:26:29,160 --> 01:26:31,151
Good luck all... Till we meet again.

966
01:26:37,720 --> 01:26:38,755
Give me some money!

967
01:26:48,280 --> 01:26:49,190
Who is he?

968
01:26:51,880 --> 01:26:53,074
Mao Tse-tung from Hu'nan.

969
01:26:54,120 --> 01:26:55,348
What a shame he's not going!

970
01:27:05,600 --> 01:27:08,433
Why did the Governor shut down the
"Shian Kian Review"?

971
01:27:09,080 --> 01:27:10,559
Because we told the truth.

972
01:27:11,440 --> 01:27:14,750
He's afraid the truth will come out

973
01:27:15,440 --> 01:27:17,795
about Chang Ching-yao being Hu'nan's public enemy.

974
01:27:18,440 --> 01:27:22,035
Workers, peasants and merchants have all suffered.

975
01:27:22,400 --> 01:27:25,437
Fellow workers, Hu'nan will not tolerate Chang!

976
01:27:25,720 --> 01:27:28,518
Hu'nan is finished with him around.

977
01:27:29,680 --> 01:27:32,638
We're only poor workers

978
01:27:32,800 --> 01:27:34,313
we have no say.

979
01:27:34,880 --> 01:27:36,199
How do you write the word "work"?

980
01:27:37,040 --> 01:27:38,917
A vertical stroke between 2 lines.

981
01:27:39,640 --> 01:27:43,076
Yes, heaven above your head
with your feet on the ground.

982
01:27:43,920 --> 01:27:45,558
The words "work" and "man" together

983
01:27:45,960 --> 01:27:47,837
make the word "heaven".

984
01:27:48,400 --> 01:27:50,994
It means the world under heaven.

985
01:27:51,680 --> 01:27:54,911
Workers and peasants will rule the world.

986
01:27:55,560 --> 01:27:58,597
Sounds too good to be true.

987
01:28:00,200 --> 01:28:01,553
This is not my idea,

988
01:28:02,080 --> 01:28:03,957
it belongs to a foreigner called Marx.

989
01:28:04,520 --> 01:28:06,033
This foreigner advocated

990
01:28:06,400 --> 01:28:09,995
equality of all men.

991
01:28:10,680 --> 01:28:12,079
Adopting this theory,

992
01:28:12,200 --> 01:28:15,556
the Russian workers now rule their own country.

993
01:28:15,960 --> 01:28:21,318
Fellow workers, the revolution Marx spoke
of will be universal.

994
01:28:21,760 --> 01:28:26,151
Chinese workers should follow suit.

995
01:28:26,720 --> 01:28:30,998
Overthrow this corrupt and evil government

996
01:28:31,320 --> 01:28:35,279
that bullied and oppressed us.

997
01:28:35,560 --> 01:28:40,509
Yes...

998
01:28:48,600 --> 01:28:51,068
Tse-tung, your telegram.

999
01:28:59,360 --> 01:29:00,918
Tse-tung...

1000
01:29:05,680 --> 01:29:07,716
the doctor said dad had a stroke,

1001
01:29:08,160 --> 01:29:10,993
he can't talk, he can't hear.

1002
01:29:16,720 --> 01:29:21,635
His health has deteriorated so much in a year...

1003
01:29:23,040 --> 01:29:27,192
Before taken ill,
dad hadn't stopped speaking of you.

1004
01:29:32,680 --> 01:29:33,795
Remember...

1005
01:29:34,880 --> 01:29:36,393
the summer of 1 91 5

1006
01:29:36,680 --> 01:29:38,432
you asked me a question?

1007
01:29:39,280 --> 01:29:40,429
All these years,

1008
01:29:41,640 --> 01:29:44,438
I've been thinking hard.

1009
01:29:46,200 --> 01:29:47,758
I'm close to having an answer.

1010
01:29:51,640 --> 01:29:52,959
But...

1011
01:30:01,640 --> 01:30:02,436
Sir...

1012
01:30:02,640 --> 01:30:03,550
Dad...

1013
01:30:27,160 --> 01:30:28,559
As my wife,

1014
01:30:29,840 --> 01:30:31,114
Iife will be tough.

1015
01:30:35,840 --> 01:30:36,909
If you're with me,

1016
01:30:38,200 --> 01:30:40,236
you won't enjoy a stable life,

1017
01:30:41,440 --> 01:30:45,353
no bridal gowns, sedan chair or banquet.

1018
01:30:52,360 --> 01:30:54,351
Not even a witness or marriage license.

1019
01:31:16,240 --> 01:31:17,798
I'm willing.

1020
01:31:26,840 --> 01:31:30,230
The Governor wishes to meet your representatives.

1021
01:31:30,440 --> 01:31:31,589
Follow me!

1022
01:31:43,960 --> 01:31:44,517
Let them go!

1023
01:31:44,680 --> 01:31:46,796
You have no right to arrest us!

1024
01:31:46,960 --> 01:31:48,598
What are you doing? Let go!

1025
01:31:48,920 --> 01:31:49,796
What do you want?

1026
01:31:49,960 --> 01:31:53,794
Let go of me!

1027
01:31:58,600 --> 01:32:00,795
Let us out!

1028
01:32:09,800 --> 01:32:11,074
In this world,

1029
01:32:11,600 --> 01:32:13,556
who are the noblest people?

1030
01:32:14,840 --> 01:32:16,068
My answer to that...

1031
01:32:18,360 --> 01:32:20,157
is the working class.

1032
01:32:22,360 --> 01:32:26,638
Food, clothes, and even houses that we live in

1033
01:32:26,800 --> 01:32:29,792
are all created by workers.

1034
01:32:30,440 --> 01:32:32,237
We slave for a living,

1035
01:32:32,760 --> 01:32:35,957
but we're not well fed, clothed or sheltered.

1036
01:32:36,520 --> 01:32:37,873
Is that fair?

1037
01:32:38,040 --> 01:32:39,109
No!

1038
01:32:39,320 --> 01:32:41,675
Of course not!

1039
01:32:42,280 --> 01:32:44,953
That's why we must unite

1040
01:32:45,160 --> 01:32:46,388
and go on strike.

1041
01:32:47,160 --> 01:32:49,071
Confront these bourgeois factory owners

1042
01:32:49,320 --> 01:32:50,753
and show them our strength.

1043
01:32:50,920 --> 01:32:52,876
Reclaim what is rightfully ours.

1044
01:32:54,440 --> 01:32:55,589
Fellow workers,

1045
01:32:56,320 --> 01:32:59,437
in the future

1046
01:32:59,720 --> 01:33:01,995
workers will rule the world.

1047
01:33:03,040 --> 01:33:10,435
Long live workers!

1048
01:33:10,680 --> 01:33:15,231
Release the students!

1049
01:33:15,760 --> 01:33:18,433
Sir, these students haven't eaten in 3 days.

1050
01:33:19,040 --> 01:33:20,075
Who's not eating?

1051
01:33:21,120 --> 01:33:22,269
Let him starve to death!

1052
01:33:22,840 --> 01:33:24,956
He has no one but himself to blame.

1053
01:33:41,840 --> 01:33:43,398
Who wrote this?

1054
01:33:44,880 --> 01:33:46,074
I did.

1055
01:33:48,840 --> 01:33:50,239
These are our latest demands.

1056
01:33:53,920 --> 01:33:57,230
The hunger strike continues until they are met.

1057
01:34:02,880 --> 01:34:05,633
We want books and newspapers.

1058
01:34:05,960 --> 01:34:07,359
- Go ahead. - Yes!

1059
01:34:08,760 --> 01:34:09,909
We want New Year dinner.

1060
01:34:10,080 --> 01:34:14,631
I'll treat all 26 of you to dinner!

1061
01:34:15,200 --> 01:34:16,349
We'll even eat outside.

1062
01:34:16,560 --> 01:34:18,198
The Awakening Society needs a place to study.

1063
01:34:19,240 --> 01:34:20,275
Certainly.

1064
01:34:22,160 --> 01:34:23,195
What's your name?

1065
01:34:26,400 --> 01:34:27,389
Chou En-lai.

1066
01:34:37,880 --> 01:34:39,029
Why did you change your mind?

1067
01:34:39,440 --> 01:34:41,032
Didn't we agree to go on hunger strike?

1068
01:34:41,200 --> 01:34:44,556
Change of tactics.
Let's prepare for a long struggle!

1069
01:34:44,960 --> 01:34:45,915
Let's eat.

1070
01:35:23,440 --> 01:35:24,509
Goodbye!

1071
01:35:26,160 --> 01:35:26,910
Mr. Ch'en!

1072
01:35:30,280 --> 01:35:32,794
"Cops are after you, follow the student, Li Ta-chao"

1073
01:35:33,200 --> 01:35:34,235
Follow me!

1074
01:35:42,240 --> 01:35:44,800
If you leave Peking while on bail

1075
01:35:45,360 --> 01:35:47,191
and get arrested again,

1076
01:35:47,360 --> 01:35:48,349
it'll be difficult to get out.

1077
01:35:48,560 --> 01:35:50,039
I'll go back to Shanghai.

1078
01:35:54,640 --> 01:35:56,551
Scholars-in-arms are hopeless.

1079
01:35:58,080 --> 01:35:59,354
Don't say that!

1080
01:36:00,680 --> 01:36:03,353
Your arrest has shaken the nation.

1081
01:36:03,680 --> 01:36:05,796
That's as big an honour as you can get!

1082
01:36:10,360 --> 01:36:11,998
What are you studying these days?

1083
01:36:13,880 --> 01:36:14,995
The Russian Revolution.

1084
01:36:20,840 --> 01:36:22,671
Hu Shih was right about you!

1085
01:36:23,680 --> 01:36:27,036
The Russian Revolution is all you care about.

1086
01:36:28,080 --> 01:36:32,392
It's the last resort when all else have failed.

1087
01:36:34,720 --> 01:36:35,675
Now tell me,

1088
01:36:37,720 --> 01:36:40,393
why model after Russia?

1089
01:36:40,720 --> 01:36:43,280
The reason why the Russians succeeded

1090
01:36:43,760 --> 01:36:45,830
was because the Bolsheviks

1091
01:36:46,000 --> 01:36:49,037
united the workers and peasants,

1092
01:36:49,200 --> 01:36:51,430
the broadest social classes.

1093
01:36:52,720 --> 01:36:55,871
To unite the nation, you must first

1094
01:36:56,600 --> 01:36:58,192
unite peasants and workers.

1095
01:36:58,640 --> 01:36:59,755
To unite them,

1096
01:37:00,600 --> 01:37:03,273
China must first have its own Bolshevik.

1097
01:37:05,640 --> 01:37:07,949
Tu-hsiu, when you get to Shanghai,

1098
01:37:08,120 --> 01:37:09,678
that's exactly what you've to do.

1099
01:37:09,920 --> 01:37:13,196
We'll split up, you take the north, I go south,

1100
01:37:13,360 --> 01:37:15,032
form our own political party at once.

1101
01:37:24,440 --> 01:37:25,395
Easy...

1102
01:37:27,280 --> 01:37:28,315
When I get to Shanghai,

1103
01:37:28,560 --> 01:37:30,596
I'll send you your favourite candy.

1104
01:37:30,920 --> 01:37:32,273
You must keep your word!

1105
01:37:36,240 --> 01:37:37,070
Take care!

1106
01:37:38,080 --> 01:37:39,069
Take care!

1107
01:38:18,960 --> 01:38:20,678
We should help China

1108
01:38:20,840 --> 01:38:23,673
build her own Bolshevik Party.

1109
01:38:23,840 --> 01:38:27,230
The committee nominates Maring to assist.

1110
01:38:28,000 --> 01:38:30,673
Excellent, go right away!

1111
01:38:32,440 --> 01:38:33,998
Bravo!

1112
01:38:41,080 --> 01:38:42,559
What does the Shanghai dispatch say?

1113
01:38:44,560 --> 01:38:46,676
Each region should send two delegates
to the congress,

1114
01:38:46,840 --> 01:38:48,637
and the caucuses in Japan and Europe

1115
01:38:48,800 --> 01:38:50,153
will each send one delegate.

1116
01:38:50,160 --> 01:38:51,309
Peking, Shanghai, Canton,

1117
01:38:51,560 --> 01:38:53,710
Ch'ang-sha, Wuhan and Tsinan
will all be represented.

1118
01:38:54,040 --> 01:38:56,156
You and Ch'en Kung-po will represent Canton.

1119
01:38:57,160 --> 01:39:00,152
You two will represent Peking.

1120
01:39:01,000 --> 01:39:01,796
Remember,

1121
01:39:01,960 --> 01:39:04,269
you're there as my personal representative.

1122
01:39:04,680 --> 01:39:05,635
Aren't you attending?

1123
01:39:06,240 --> 01:39:08,356
The Comintern is attaching great importance to it.

1124
01:39:08,680 --> 01:39:11,353
If neither you nor Mr. Ch'en attend,

1125
01:39:11,560 --> 01:39:13,039
what's the point of having the congress?

1126
01:39:14,720 --> 01:39:16,392
Apologise to Comrade Maring for me.

1127
01:39:18,440 --> 01:39:22,035
Students are borrowing more books
for summer vacation.

1128
01:39:22,520 --> 01:39:23,873
I can't leave as Head Librarian.

1129
01:39:24,240 --> 01:39:27,038
I disagree with the Comintern on many issues,

1130
01:39:27,600 --> 01:39:29,830
if we argue during the congress

1131
01:39:30,160 --> 01:39:31,832
there will be no way back.

1132
01:39:32,000 --> 01:39:32,591
I see.

1133
01:39:32,760 --> 01:39:33,670
Remember,

1134
01:39:34,720 --> 01:39:37,871
Ch'en Tu-hsiu and I must act in unanimity.

1135
01:39:38,160 --> 01:39:39,036
I understand.

1136
01:39:56,600 --> 01:39:58,909
This should be enough for a month,

1137
01:40:00,840 --> 01:40:03,513
when you get to Shanghai, spend when you have to.

1138
01:40:06,600 --> 01:40:08,079
Dad left this,

1139
01:40:10,760 --> 01:40:11,875
you have it.

1140
01:40:14,440 --> 01:40:15,555
No, you keep it.

1141
01:40:16,800 --> 01:40:19,394
Don't be late for the congress.

1142
01:40:20,920 --> 01:40:21,830
No!

1143
01:40:22,400 --> 01:40:25,995
Just take it.

1144
01:40:45,280 --> 01:40:46,315
I'm leaving,

1145
01:40:49,720 --> 01:40:51,199
take good care of yourself.

1146
01:41:21,760 --> 01:41:23,432
Let me introduce myself,

1147
01:41:23,920 --> 01:41:25,512
Chang Kuo-t'ao from Peking.

1148
01:41:26,640 --> 01:41:28,517
Liu Jen-ching, also from Peking.

1149
01:41:28,680 --> 01:41:31,114
I'm Li Han-chun from Shanghai.

1150
01:41:31,640 --> 01:41:32,993
Li Ta from Shanghai.

1151
01:41:33,160 --> 01:41:34,991
Teng En-ming from Tsinan.

1152
01:41:35,520 --> 01:41:37,192
Wang Chin-mei from Tsinan.

1153
01:41:37,880 --> 01:41:39,154
Tung Pi-wu from Wuhan.

1154
01:41:39,880 --> 01:41:41,313
Ch'en Tan-ch'iu from Wuhan.

1155
01:41:42,160 --> 01:41:43,912
Chou Fo-hai from Japan.

1156
01:41:45,320 --> 01:41:48,710
Pao Hui-seng, representing Ch'en Tu-hsiu.
Nice to meet you.

1157
01:41:48,840 --> 01:41:50,831
Ho Shu-heng from Chang-sha.

1158
01:41:51,240 --> 01:41:54,357
- This comrade from Chang-sha is...
- Tse-tung,

1159
01:41:55,280 --> 01:41:56,030
it's been a while.

1160
01:41:56,200 --> 01:41:57,315
Indeed, Kuo-t'ao.

1161
01:41:58,720 --> 01:42:00,199
My apologies, gentlemen...

1162
01:42:00,360 --> 01:42:02,191
Sorry for being late.

1163
01:42:02,840 --> 01:42:04,796
Hello, everyone.

1164
01:42:05,560 --> 01:42:07,835
I'm Ch'en Kung-po from Canton.

1165
01:42:08,200 --> 01:42:11,272
Who's the lovely lady?

1166
01:42:11,520 --> 01:42:12,077
My wife.

1167
01:42:12,240 --> 01:42:14,071
Greetings, I'm Li Li-chuang.

1168
01:42:14,240 --> 01:42:16,549
But we can't accommodate a couple...

1169
01:42:16,760 --> 01:42:17,158
I'm sorry...

1170
01:42:17,320 --> 01:42:19,356
We've a room at Tatung Hotel across the street.

1171
01:42:19,560 --> 01:42:20,709
Bringing your spouse to the congress?

1172
01:42:22,120 --> 01:42:23,030
Everyone...

1173
01:42:23,200 --> 01:42:24,872
This is my wife, Wang Hui-wu.

1174
01:42:25,520 --> 01:42:27,351
I'm working the reception.

1175
01:42:27,560 --> 01:42:29,039
Look for me if you need anything.

1176
01:42:29,880 --> 01:42:32,599
We've all had long trips, get some rest.

1177
01:42:32,880 --> 01:42:34,233
Meet at my brother's place tomorrow.

1178
01:42:34,400 --> 01:42:36,994
1 06 rue Wantz.

1179
01:42:38,000 --> 01:42:38,955
I'm most honoured

1180
01:42:39,160 --> 01:42:41,833
to represent Ch'en Tu-hsiu and Li Ta-chao

1181
01:42:42,000 --> 01:42:44,798
to chair the First National Congress.

1182
01:42:44,960 --> 01:42:45,915
Let me introduce to you

1183
01:42:46,840 --> 01:42:47,795
Comrade Maring,

1184
01:42:47,920 --> 01:42:50,354
an observer from Comintern.

1185
01:42:50,840 --> 01:42:52,751
Mao Tse-tung will be our secretary.

1186
01:42:55,200 --> 01:42:58,078
The first item on the agenda

1187
01:42:58,520 --> 01:42:59,669
is to decide on the name of the party.

1188
01:43:00,240 --> 01:43:04,358
Our view regarding the name of the party
is clear-cut.

1189
01:43:04,920 --> 01:43:07,070
From the "The Communist Manifesto",

1190
01:43:07,240 --> 01:43:08,992
we adopt the word "Communist"

1191
01:43:09,360 --> 01:43:11,510
and call it the Chinese Communist Party.

1192
01:43:12,080 --> 01:43:15,390
In his letter to Tse-tung,
Ts'ai Ho-san is also in favour.

1193
01:43:21,600 --> 01:43:25,673
Maring wants to know Li Ta-chao's view.

1194
01:43:31,680 --> 01:43:33,272
Mr. Li's preference is

1195
01:43:34,240 --> 01:43:35,229
Chinese Communist Party.

1196
01:43:35,240 --> 01:43:36,116
I agree.

1197
01:43:36,440 --> 01:43:37,714
Agreed.

1198
01:43:39,440 --> 01:43:44,195
Agreed.

1199
01:43:46,120 --> 01:43:47,189
Unanimously passed.

1200
01:44:04,600 --> 01:44:05,271
Rickshaw-man,

1201
01:44:06,360 --> 01:44:08,271
Tung Fang Hotel on Nanking Road.

1202
01:44:08,440 --> 01:44:10,670
Let's go to Palace Hotel instead.

1203
01:44:10,880 --> 01:44:12,677
We're switching hotels?

1204
01:44:12,840 --> 01:44:14,034
We're being followed.

1205
01:44:14,440 --> 01:44:16,032
Be careful, don't look around.

1206
01:44:16,520 --> 01:44:17,669
Palace Hotel.

1207
01:44:17,960 --> 01:44:18,790
Got it!

1208
01:44:42,440 --> 01:44:44,874
Is there another exit?

1209
01:44:45,080 --> 01:44:47,958
There's a back entrance for the staff.

1210
01:44:48,160 --> 01:44:50,151
Wait for us there in five minutes.

1211
01:44:50,320 --> 01:44:51,355
Sure!

1212
01:44:57,400 --> 01:45:02,599
Why are we being followed everywhere?

1213
01:45:02,760 --> 01:45:03,749
I'm sorry, sir.

1214
01:45:04,200 --> 01:45:05,838
The first floor is full,

1215
01:45:06,120 --> 01:45:07,235
is the second floor alright?

1216
01:45:08,560 --> 01:45:09,515
Alright!

1217
01:45:23,760 --> 01:45:24,590
Jump!

1218
01:45:39,600 --> 01:45:41,875
Stupid idiots...

1219
01:45:46,920 --> 01:45:47,716
Go look for them!

1220
01:45:47,880 --> 01:45:50,189
Find them in three days or else!

1221
01:45:50,360 --> 01:45:53,511
Sir, my brother is with the Green Gang

1222
01:45:53,840 --> 01:45:56,559
finding someone in Shanghai is a piece of cake.

1223
01:46:00,240 --> 01:46:03,312
The Peking caucus has 1 3 members,

1224
01:46:03,560 --> 01:46:06,518
including Li Ta-chao, Chang Kuo-t'ao,

1225
01:46:06,720 --> 01:46:08,597
Lo Zhang-lung, Liu Jen-ch'ing,

1226
01:46:08,800 --> 01:46:11,439
Ch'en Te-jung, Teng Chung-hsia,

1227
01:46:11,720 --> 01:46:15,633
Kao Chun-yu, Miu Po-ying, Ho Meng-hsiung,

1228
01:46:15,800 --> 01:46:18,439
Chu Wu-shan, Fan Hung-chieh, Wu Ju-ming.

1229
01:46:19,640 --> 01:46:21,119
Heads up, everyone!

1230
01:46:23,040 --> 01:46:24,155
A draft platform of the CCP

1231
01:46:24,320 --> 01:46:27,517
is hereby pronounced
for delegates to comment and discuss.

1232
01:46:28,640 --> 01:46:31,154
Proletariat must join force
with the revolutionary army

1233
01:46:31,440 --> 01:46:33,635
and overthrow the bourgeois regime;

1234
01:46:33,880 --> 01:46:35,632
they must help the working class

1235
01:46:35,800 --> 01:46:38,439
until the class system is abolished,

1236
01:46:38,640 --> 01:46:40,676
and until the class struggle has ended.

1237
01:46:40,880 --> 01:46:44,316
Meaning, when class system is finally abolished,

1238
01:46:44,520 --> 01:46:46,238
a proletariat dictatorship will be established.

1239
01:46:46,880 --> 01:46:48,359
Liaise with the Comintern,

1240
01:46:48,640 --> 01:46:50,232
and adopt the Soviet model.

1241
01:46:50,400 --> 01:46:53,233
Unite workers, peasants and soldiers

1242
01:46:53,400 --> 01:46:56,995
and adopt social revolution as our goal.

1243
01:46:57,440 --> 01:46:59,556
Those who accept the Party's platform and policies,

1244
01:46:59,720 --> 01:47:01,551
and willing to be loyal members,

1245
01:47:01,720 --> 01:47:03,278
upon the introduction of a Party member,

1246
01:47:03,680 --> 01:47:05,511
regardless of gender and nationality

1247
01:47:05,680 --> 01:47:07,272
can be admitted as Party members

1248
01:47:07,800 --> 01:47:08,949
and become our comrades.

1249
01:47:09,360 --> 01:47:11,078
But...

1250
01:47:11,800 --> 01:47:13,552
before their initiation into the Party,

1251
01:47:13,720 --> 01:47:15,312
they must sever all ties

1252
01:47:15,520 --> 01:47:17,238
with other parties and organisations

1253
01:47:17,400 --> 01:47:18,799
whose platforms are contradictory to ours.

1254
01:47:19,160 --> 01:47:20,673
Tomorrow is the last day of the congress,

1255
01:47:20,840 --> 01:47:22,159
the main agenda

1256
01:47:22,320 --> 01:47:25,073
is to adopt the platform
and election of the Central Committee.

1257
01:47:25,240 --> 01:47:27,037
Comrades Maring and Nikolsky

1258
01:47:27,200 --> 01:47:28,997
will attend tomorrow's closing session.

1259
01:47:36,240 --> 01:47:37,116
Rickshaw!

1260
01:48:23,280 --> 01:48:27,034
Sorry, we had to make a detour.

1261
01:48:27,760 --> 01:48:28,590
Is everyone here?

1262
01:48:29,240 --> 01:48:31,117
Chou Fo-hai is in the toilet,

1263
01:48:31,280 --> 01:48:32,110
he'll be right back.

1264
01:48:32,560 --> 01:48:33,436
It's that Chou again!

1265
01:48:34,120 --> 01:48:34,916
Let's not wait.

1266
01:48:36,280 --> 01:48:37,633
The draft platform we tabled yesterday,

1267
01:48:38,080 --> 01:48:40,230
can continue to be discussed now.

1268
01:48:40,840 --> 01:48:41,590
I have a comment.

1269
01:48:42,280 --> 01:48:44,157
Regarding nationality...

1270
01:48:56,360 --> 01:48:57,110
Can I help you?

1271
01:48:57,800 --> 01:48:58,596
Looking for someone?

1272
01:48:58,960 --> 01:48:59,676
What do you want?

1273
01:49:02,040 --> 01:49:02,836
Who are you looking for?

1274
01:49:03,000 --> 01:49:04,353
Chairman Wang of the Social League.

1275
01:49:05,000 --> 01:49:06,399
There's no Social League

1276
01:49:06,600 --> 01:49:07,510
or Chairman Wang.

1277
01:49:13,800 --> 01:49:14,994
I'm sorry...

1278
01:49:25,440 --> 01:49:27,556
Maring calls for an immediate recess.

1279
01:49:29,160 --> 01:49:30,513
I agree with Comrade Maring.

1280
01:49:30,800 --> 01:49:31,835
Let's adjourne.

1281
01:49:48,200 --> 01:49:50,509
This is my home. What are you doing here?

1282
01:49:54,320 --> 01:49:56,788
Why do you organise meeting in your house?

1283
01:49:57,200 --> 01:50:01,113
What meeting? I was entertaining guests.

1284
01:50:01,280 --> 01:50:04,636
That two are from which country?

1285
01:50:04,800 --> 01:50:05,789
Which two?

1286
01:50:06,080 --> 01:50:07,752
The two foreigners.

1287
01:50:07,920 --> 01:50:09,990
They're Dutch.

1288
01:50:15,200 --> 01:50:17,236
Pack up and be ready to move out!

1289
01:50:28,200 --> 01:50:28,996
Sir.

1290
01:50:32,960 --> 01:50:34,518
What do you do for a living?

1291
01:50:35,640 --> 01:50:36,550
Professor.

1292
01:50:38,080 --> 01:50:38,990
Him?

1293
01:50:39,720 --> 01:50:40,755
My colleague.

1294
01:50:41,680 --> 01:50:46,037
Today I can close your house and catch your people.

1295
01:50:46,440 --> 01:50:49,955
Because you are teaching in university,
I'll let you free.

1296
01:50:51,160 --> 01:50:53,993
If not, you will burn yourself.

1297
01:50:55,000 --> 01:50:56,115
I won't.

1298
01:51:10,320 --> 01:51:11,116
How is it?

1299
01:51:12,280 --> 01:51:13,269
It's fine.

1300
01:51:13,600 --> 01:51:15,079
Comrade Maring said we must leave Shanghai.

1301
01:51:15,440 --> 01:51:16,793
I suggest we go to Chiahsing

1302
01:51:16,960 --> 01:51:19,235
rent a boat for the meeting.

1303
01:51:19,400 --> 01:51:21,072
Is Maring coming?

1304
01:51:21,240 --> 01:51:22,309
He's too obvious a target,

1305
01:51:22,520 --> 01:51:24,192
for our safety, he's not going.

1306
01:51:24,360 --> 01:51:25,156
Alright!

1307
01:51:25,680 --> 01:51:26,271
What time do we leave?

1308
01:51:26,400 --> 01:51:28,391
There's a train tomorrow at 1 0:00am.

1309
01:51:29,280 --> 01:51:31,111
Does Ch'en Kung-po know?

1310
01:51:31,280 --> 01:51:32,429
I'll go get him tomorrow morning.

1311
01:51:37,520 --> 01:51:41,559
Are you under surveillance?

1312
01:51:41,760 --> 01:51:43,637
Probably not, it was an accident.

1313
01:51:44,080 --> 01:51:45,115
Let's go home.

1314
01:51:45,920 --> 01:51:46,989
The meeting is not yet over.

1315
01:51:48,320 --> 01:51:51,596
To form a national party with just 50 people,

1316
01:51:51,760 --> 01:51:53,079
this has to be a joke!

1317
01:52:59,880 --> 01:53:00,869
A gun!

1318
01:53:10,960 --> 01:53:11,631
Don't stare!

1319
01:54:34,640 --> 01:54:35,993
Homicide at Tatung Hotel!

1320
01:54:36,640 --> 01:54:37,595
Tatung Hotel?

1321
01:54:39,880 --> 01:54:41,233
That's where Ch'en Kung-po stays!

1322
01:54:46,200 --> 01:54:48,634
Kung-po left for Kwangtung already.

1323
01:54:48,800 --> 01:54:50,279
Yesterday two people died at their hotel.

1324
01:54:50,520 --> 01:54:52,431
His wife was petrified. So they left.

1325
01:54:53,280 --> 01:54:54,759
It was a lovers' suicide pact!

1326
01:54:56,200 --> 01:54:57,235
Cowards!

1327
01:54:59,000 --> 01:54:59,830
Let's go.

1328
01:55:22,320 --> 01:55:25,357
Comrades, we have reached the critical hours.

1329
01:55:25,640 --> 01:55:26,993
The last item on the agenda,

1330
01:55:27,440 --> 01:55:28,998
is to elect the Party Central Committee.

1331
01:55:29,560 --> 01:55:30,675
Under democratic principles,

1332
01:55:30,960 --> 01:55:32,075
we shall vote for

1333
01:55:32,240 --> 01:55:34,674
members of the Central Committee.

1334
01:55:44,360 --> 01:55:45,793
We should have 1 3 delegates,

1335
01:55:45,960 --> 01:55:47,234
but only 12 are in attendance.

1336
01:55:48,360 --> 01:55:49,190
After the vote,

1337
01:55:49,440 --> 01:55:53,274
Ch'en Tu-hsiu, Chang Kuo-t'ao and Li Ta

1338
01:55:53,440 --> 01:55:55,271
are elected Central Committee members,

1339
01:55:55,600 --> 01:55:58,398
Ch'en Tu-hsiu is named General Secretary.

1340
01:55:58,880 --> 01:55:59,869
Meeting is concluded.

1341
01:56:00,880 --> 01:56:01,630
Comrades,

1342
01:56:02,040 --> 01:56:04,395
I'd like to recite from "The Communist Manifesto"

1343
01:56:04,680 --> 01:56:06,352
to illustrate my thrill and excitement.

1344
01:56:09,040 --> 01:56:12,191
The Communists disdain to conceal

1345
01:56:12,360 --> 01:56:14,828
their aims and views.

1346
01:56:15,360 --> 01:56:16,679
They openly declare

1347
01:56:17,040 --> 01:56:19,600
that their ends can be attained

1348
01:56:19,760 --> 01:56:21,990
only by the forcible overthrow

1349
01:56:22,160 --> 01:56:22,637
of all existing social conditions.

1350
01:56:22,800 --> 01:56:24,199
Let the ruling classes tremble

1351
01:56:24,360 --> 01:56:26,510
at a communist revolution.

1352
01:56:27,040 --> 01:56:30,316
The proletarians have nothing to lose
but their chains.

1353
01:56:30,800 --> 01:56:33,439
They have a world to win.

1354
01:56:33,760 --> 01:56:36,354
Proletarians of all countries, unite.

1355
01:56:37,040 --> 01:56:39,838
Proletarians of all countries, unite.

1356
01:56:40,000 --> 01:56:42,753
Proletarians of all countries, unite...

1357
01:56:43,120 --> 01:56:46,078
Proletarians of all countries...

1358
01:56:46,280 --> 01:56:47,315
...unite

